== Regular Festival == The annual festival of Nagakusa Tenjinsha was held on the 25th day of the first month of the [[Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|Lunar calendar]] from Meio 3 to {{ill|1910|en|1910|qid=Q2075|lt=Meiji 43|1=1910}}, when the shrine was founded, but now it is held on the Sunday immediately before {{ill|February 25|en|February 25|qid=Q2356|lt=February 25|1=February 25}}. The {{ill|Nigori|en|Nigori|qid=Q60995819|lt=Doburoku|1=Nigori}} festival is held as the annual festival.
== Doburoku Festival == The {{ill|Nigori|en|Nigori|qid=Q60995819|lt=Doburoku|1=Nigori}} Festival at Nagakusa Tenjinsha is a {{ill|Festival|en|Festival|qid=Q132241|lt=Ritual|1=Festival}} held as an annual festival, and is designated as a Tangible Folk Cultural Property by Obu City. <ref>{{Cite web |date= |title=長草天神社どぶろくまつり |url=http://www.city.obu.aichi.jp/rekimin/bunkazai/shitei_bunkazai/bunkazai_kaisetsu/s22.html |access-date=2013-05-29 |publisher=大府市 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305034539/http://www.city.obu.aichi.jp/rekimin/bunkazai/shitei_bunkazai/bunkazai_kaisetsu/s22.html |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name="chunichi2016221">{{Cite news |last=石井宏昌 |date=2016-02-21 |title=知多半島 宝モノ語り 長草天神社のどぶろく祭り 地域住民が醸成見守る |page=朝刊 知多版 20 |work=[[:en:中日新聞|中日新聞]] |publisher=中日新聞社}}</ref> <ref name="chunichi2021124">{{Cite news |last=栗山真寛 |date=2021-01-24 |title=あいちの民話を訪ねて 神事コロナ禍の今こそ |page=朝刊 県内版 12 |work=[[:en:中日新聞|中日新聞]] |publisher=中日新聞社}}</ref>。
